Detailed Description

The FileInfo class holds information about each file or directory contained.

The FileInfo class is used in a list to contain information about all the files and directories contained in the package.

It contains the following information SourceName - This corresponds to the Name of the file or directory in the package if SourceName is a directory then all the files in it will be copied. DestinationDirectory - This corresponds to where the file or directory should be installed on the users computer. If it is a directory it MUST end with a backslash or else it will be interpreted as a filename. The SourceName and Dirctory
